# Dam Research: Todo

## Empirical Analysis

### Baseline
- [ ] Run baseline DiD at county level for economic outcomes (GDP, nighttime lights, firm output)
- [ ] Classify dams by primary purpose: flood control, irrigation/water supply, hydropower
- [ ] Run heterogeneous effects by dam type in the baseline DiD

### Upstream/Downstream Analysis
- [ ] Construct upstream/downstream spatial indicators relative to dam placement
- [ ] Run upstream vs. downstream DiD for energy-intensive industries — test for differential impact
- [ ] Run upstream vs. downstream DiD for pollution outcomes — test for differential impact
- [ ] Run within-location before/after comparison: upstream vs. downstream for the same dam site

## Data

### Economic & Firm Data
- [ ] Obtain county-level data on economic outcomes (GDP, firm output, nighttime lights)
- [ ] Obtain firm-level data with industry codes to identify energy-intensive and water-intensive sectors

### Dam Data
- [ ] Obtain dam registry with dam type classification and construction dates
- [ ] Define upstream/downstream catchment areas using river network / DEM data

### Environmental Data
- [ ] Obtain pollution data (PM2.5, SO₂, emissions) at county level

## Welfare & Model
- [ ] Build quantitative model to separately identify and aggregate the three dam channels (flood protection, water supply, electricity)
- [ ] Incorporate pollution as a negative externality in the welfare calculation
- [ ] Quantify relative welfare magnitudes across dam types and channels
